Because of the complex and abstract nature of love, discourse on love is commonly reduced to a [[thought-terminating cliché]], and there are a number of common [[proverb]]s regarding love, from [[Virgil|Virgil's]] "[[Love Conquers All|Love conquers all]]" to the [[The Beatles|Beatles']] "[[All You Need is Love|All you need is love]]." [[Bertrand Russell]] describes love as a condition of "absolute value," as opposed to [[relative value]].
